cs.LO, cs.FL, cs.PL, cs.DS, cs.SE 

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with algorithmic synthesis of recursive programs using Boolean formulas and transition monoids, which are closely related to logic. 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is also a likely category as the paper deals with games played on the infinite graph of sentential forms induced by a context-free grammar and winning conditions based on inclusion in the language of a finite automaton. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is a possible category as the paper deals with algorithmic synthesis of recursive programs. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possible category as the paper deals with algorithmic synthesis and computation of winning strategies. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is a possible category as the paper deals with algorithmic synthesis of recursive programs and optimization techniques.
